Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 15:03:19 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(ui): per-server checkboxes inside a VLESS subscription
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Patch 15 — lets the user pick which servers from a fetched
subscription should actually feed the sing-box urltest selector,
instead of always using all of them.

  * SubscriptionCache: SubscriptionServer { params, enabled } replaces
    the bare VlessParams in entries; SubscriptionEntry::enabledParams()
    returns only the enabled subset. JSON schema for each entry now
    stores [{ "url": "vless://...", "enabled": true }, ...]; legacy
    flat string lists still load (everything defaults to enabled).
    setServers() preserves the per-server enabled flag for vless URLs
    that survive a re-fetch and defaults brand-new ones to enabled.
    New setServerEnabled(url, index, bool) for in-place toggles.
  * ProxyData::forUse() for Type::VlessSubscription now hands
    enabledParams() to the bridge — disabled servers are excluded
    from the urltest config.
  * ProxyBox edit dialog: replaces the FlatLabel server list with
    a Ui::VerticalLayout of per-server Ui::Checkbox widgets, rebuilt
    on cache change. Each checkbox shows
    "1. server-de  45ms  ← active" and toggling it persists the
    new enabled flag immediately. Status header reads
    "12 server(s), 9 enabled — refreshed YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM ·
    click Apply to use changes" so the user knows toggles only take
    effect on the next sidecar restart.
  * ProxiesBoxController row label now reads
    "active: <server-name>" / "sidecar running, 9/12 enabled" /
    "9/12 server(s) enabled" / "(no cache — open & refresh)".
